FBIS4-62218 "drsov093_b_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-093 Daily Report 13 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Communist Leader Announces Opposition To Unite Communist Leader Announces Opposition To Unite LD1305084794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 0800 GMT 13 May 94 LD1305084794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] Russian Communist Party leader Gennadiy Zyuganov announced yesterday that the opposition intends to unite. He said consultations between opposition movements will culminate in a national gathering at the end of May. Zyuganov also disclosed that future plans include preparation of a joint action program for supporters of a people's state in all parties and movements belonging to the united opposition.
